summary:
Originating from a background in dairy farming, I studied Tropical Animal Husbandry at Wageningen University (WU). After my MSc, I worked in farmers' training and rural development, in university education, and in livestock systems research in Burkina Faso, Ivory Coast and Mali for 19 years. From 2000 to 2005, I developed student centred MSc courses at WU, where since 2003, I managed collaborative research and development programs in natural resource management and sustainable aquaculture (including environmental impact assessment), and supervise PhD and MSc students in the tropics. In 2007, I defended a PhD on Farmers Motivation for Integrated Farming Systems. Thereafter I managed several large research programs and guided PhD students mainly in Indonesia and Vietnam until my retirement in September 2019. My last projects funded by NWO-WOTRO (ALEGAMS, PASMI & Mangrove-Polders) and my continuing support to 'Building with Nature Indonesia' focuses on mangrove recovery and sustainable shrimp aquaculture.
As freelancer I did and hope to do feasibility studies, assessments and planning of livestock research and development projects in several Asian and Africa countries using participatory techniques, both in French and English as lately in Rwanda and Mali. My specialisations:
- Formulation, and midterm and final impact assessments of animal husbandry projects;
- Technical & socio-economic assessment of innovation / change on fish-crop-livestock farms;
- Participatory research and education for sustainable livestock and rangeland development.
And, together with my wife, I give workshops scientific writing.

profile_positions.description:
Support to Rural Development through monitoring (MTR), formulation and evaluation / review of Development and Research for Development projects (Below between brackets: language; donor):
2019-ongoing: I supervise the monitoring of the aquaculture component and its association to mangrove, for Building-with-Nature in Demak, Semarang, Java, Indonesia. Pro-deo I advise 2 PhDs of Universitas Diponegoro.  (English / Wetlands International).
2014: Final evaluation of the Regional Project on Sustainable Managementof Endemic Livestock in four West African countries, PRoGeBE (in both English and French; AfDB and UNDP)
2013: Review of options to support livestock development in West Africa (English; NL) 
2013: Feasibility study of dairy processing in Mopti, Mali (Francais; CARE international)
2012: Evaluation du projet Appui au Petit Elevage (APEL) au Rwanda (English/French; CTB);
2010: Final Review of WorldFish' selection and breeding program (English; EC);
2010: Evaluation et Formulation du projet de Sélection et multiplication du Zébu Azawak au Mali (Francais; CTB);
2009: Formulation du projet de l' Elevage du Zébu Azawak au Burkina Faso (Francais); Lux-Dev);
2008: Review of the Environmental impact of pangasius in the Mekong Delta (R)
2005: Review of PROCORDEL, livestock research in West-Africa (English/French; EC);
2001&2002: Forage for small-holders in SE Asia (English; ADB/CIAT);
1989: MTR du Technology development in the Toma project, Burkina Faso (Francais; SNV)
1984: MTR of the SNV support to agriculture extension in north Burkina Faso (Francais; SNV)

Manage research collaboration projects with SE Asian institutes in Indonesia and Vietnam;
Support the development of competency oriented curricula in Benin, Vietnam and Myanmar;
Study sustainable farming systems and aquaculture planning and policy making;
Support gender mainstreaming in national policies;
Supervise PhDs studying aquaculture and climate change;
Member of the Employees & University Council at Wageningen UR.

Studied cost-benefit analysis, micro-, macro-, environmental- and development economics;
Developed and lectured in three new MSc courses for Animal Production Systems;
Lead a study on alternatives for anti-biotics in animal health management; 
Lectured Socio-Economics of tropical animal production systems in Antwerpen.

As a team member I:
•	planned and participated in farming system research on: Dry season feeding of cattle; Range land management; Fodder production, storing and treatment; Innovation of small ruminant housing and husbandry; 
•	analysed data and published results on: Herd surveys; Manure production; Cattle kraaling, Sustainable mixed production systems;
•	participated in research teams on: Village resource management; Management of soil fertility; Management of small farmers' enterprises;
•	developed programs and notes for extension services, and
•	edited a book on livestock research in Southern Mali (1/1996 to 4/1996).
As interim team-leader I participated in the restructuring of the research institutes and the identification of researchable issues.

For the RUG/UO/IDR project, Animal Nutrition, I:
•	Supervised the construction of laboratory and the chemical analyses;
•	Planned and participated in research on animal nutrition and pasture management;
•	Wrote project annual financial plans and annual reports;
•	Lectured and prepared course readers on “Environment and Nutrition”;
From 1987 to 1990 I was also the team-leader of the RUG/UO project, encompassing five subprograms at the University of Ouagadougou.  As team-leader, I facilitated communication between the Universities, with the Embassy and supervised transfer of financial responsibility.
I headed two groups of experts that wrote reports for the Dutch Embassy on the future of animal traction and of livestock production in Burkina Faso.
